    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl mb-6 leading-tight">Internet health test: is your business easy to find online?</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">This simple internet health test helps local businesses spot problems in Google visibility, local SEO, website trust, social media activity, and conversion paths.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<article class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5">
    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">You do not need advanced tools to know whether your online presence needs attention. Start by checking what a real customer would see when they search, compare, and decide.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Test 1: Search your business name</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Does your Google Business Profile appear? Are the phone number, hours, website, and photos correct? If not, your local SEO foundation needs work.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Test 2: Search your service plus your city</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Search phrases like “plumber Port St. Lucie” or “salon near me.” If competitors appear and you do not, you may need stronger service pages, reviews, and local content.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Test 3: Open your website on a phone</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Your website should load quickly, explain what you do, and make it easy to call, message, or request a quote. If customers have to hunt for contact information, you are losing leads.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Test 4: Check your reviews and social proof</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Recent reviews, real photos, and testimonials help customers trust you. If your best work is not visible online, people may choose a competitor with stronger proof.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Test 5: Look at your last social post</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Social media marketing does not have to be daily, but it should show that your business is active. Old or inconsistent posts can create doubt.</p>
      <div class="rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-10 my-12" style="background:var(--primary-lt)">
        <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4" style="color:var(--primary-dk)">Score your internet health</h2>
        <ul class="checklist mb-0">
          <li>5 strong answers: you have a solid foundation.</li>
          <li>3-4 strong answers: focus on the weak spots.</li>
          <li>0-2 strong answers: your online presence likely needs a full cleanup.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">If your score is low, start with <a href="/en/blog/internet-marketing-services-small-business/" style="color:var(--primary)">internet marketing services for small businesses</a> or ask AAA Impressions for a simple review.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
